@marado No need for any apologies 😅 Super glad to have someone like you around and welcome back btw to Yarn.social / Twtxt 🤗
I think there was a good reason to only allow the # prev field to be relative, so that feed authors (malicious ones) couldn’t just arbitrarily point a feed to some other random feed that wasn’t there or something. I think @movq wrote the spec if I’m not mistaken. I agreed with it at the time, I think I still do and yarnd fully implements it as of a few weeks ago.
Why do you think redirects won’t work for deleted feeds/accounts? I’ve seen that before I think on Bitbucket of all places, where if you delete a repo, you can tell the system where the new location will be.

